{"0":"Perfect! The JSON is valid. Let me provide the final deliverables as requested:\n\n<<<RESULT_JSON>>>\n{\n  \"task_id\": \"03_Procedure_Transfer_task_12_log_triage_pattern_reuse\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"procedure\": {\n    \"name\": \"Log Triage Pattern Reuse\",\n    \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n    \"description\": \"Standardized approach for analyzing and triaging system logs with reusable patterns\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"step_1\",\n        \"name\": \"Log Collection\",\n        \"description\": \"Gather logs from specified sources with consistent formatting\",\n        \"commands\": [\n          \"find /var/log -name '*.log' -mtime -1\",\n          \"journalctl --since '1 hour ago' --no-pager\",\n          \"dmesg -T | tail -100\"\n        ],\n        \"output_format\": \"timestamp,level,source,message\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"step_2\", \n        \"name\": \"Severity Classification\",\n        \"description\": \"Categorize log entries by severity level\",\n        \"patterns\": {\n          \"critical\": [\"FATAL\", \"CRITICAL\", \"PANIC\", \"EMERGENCY\"],\n          \"error\": [\"ERROR\", \"ERR\", \"EXCEPTION\"],\n          \"warning\": [\"WARN\", \"WARNING\", \"ALERT\"],\n          \"info\": [\"INFO\", \"INFORMATION\"],\n          \"debug\": [\"DEBUG\", \"TRACE\"]\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"step_3\",\n        \"name\": \"Pattern Matching\",\n        \"description\": \"Identify common error patterns and known issues\",\n        \"patterns\": {\n          \"out_of_memory\": [\"Out of memory\", \"OOM\", \"memory allocation failed\"],\n          \"disk_full\": [\"No space left\", \"Disk full\", \"ENOSPC\"],\n          \"permission_denied\": [\"Permission denied\", \"EACCES\", \"access denied\"],\n          \"connection_refused\": [\"Connection refused\", \"ECONNREFUSED\", \"Connection reset\"],\n          \"timeout\": [\"Timeout\", \"ETIMEDOUT\", \"Connection timed out\"]\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"step_4\",\n        \"name\": \"Triage Decision\",\n        \"description\": \"Make triage decisions based on severity and pattern analysis\",\n        \"rules\": [\n          \"Critical errors require immediate investigation\",\n          \"Connection timeouts may indicate network issues\",\n          \"Permission errors suggest access control problems\",\n          \"Memory issues require resource monitoring\"\n        ]\n      }\n    ],\n    \"reusability\": {\n      \"parameters\": [\"log_source\", \"time_range\", \"severity_threshold\"],\n      \"output_formats\": [\"json\", \"csv\", \"text_summary\"],\n      \"integration_points\": [\"monitoring_systems\", \"alerting_pipelines\", \"dashboards\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-04-19T01:32:51Z\",\n  \"output_dir\": \"/tmp_workspace/results\"\n}\n<<<END_RESULT_JSON>>>\n\n<<<SUMMARY_MD>>>\n# Log Triage Pattern Reuse - Summary\n\n## Overview\nThis procedure provides a standardized, reusable approach for analyzing and triaging system logs. The pattern-based methodology ensures consistent log analysis across different systems and scenarios.\n\n## Key Components\n\n### 1. Log Collection\nThe procedure starts with systematic log collection from multiple sources:\n- System logs (`/var/log/*.log`)\n- Journal entries (systemd journal)\n- Kernel messages (dmesg)\n\n### 2. Severity Classification\nLogs are categorized into five severity levels:\n- **Critical**: Fatal errors requiring immediate attention\n- **Error**: Standard errors that need investigation\n- **Warning**: Potential issues that should be monitored\n- **Info**: Informational messages for context\n- **Debug**: Detailed debugging information\n\n### 3. Pattern Matching\nCommon error patterns are identified using keyword matching:\n- Memory issues (OOM, allocation failures)\n- Disk space problems (ENOSPC, disk full)\n- Permission errors (EACCES, access denied)\n- Network issues (connection refused, timeouts)\n\n### 4. Triage Decision\nBased on severity and pattern analysis, appropriate actions are recommended:\n- Critical errors trigger immediate alerts\n- Connection issues suggest network investigation\n- Permission errors indicate access control review\n- Memory issues require resource monitoring\n\n## Reusability Features\n\n### Parameterization\nThe procedure accepts configurable parameters:\n- `log_source`: Specify which logs to analyze\n- `time_range`: Define the analysis timeframe\n- `severity_threshold`: Set minimum severity level\n\n### Output Formats\nResults can be exported in multiple formats:\n- JSON for programmatic processing\n- CSV for spreadsheet analysis\n- Text summary for human review\n\n### Integration Points\nThe procedure integrates with:\n- Monitoring systems for automated alerting\n- Alerting pipelines for notification workflows\n- Dashboards for visual representation\n\n## Usage Example\n\n```bash\n# Basic log triage\n./log_triage_procedure.sh --source /var/log --time-range \"1 hour\" --severity warning\n\n# Export results\n./log_triage_procedure.sh --format json --output results.json\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n1. **Consistency**: Standardized approach across all systems\n2. **Efficiency**: Reusable patterns reduce analysis time\n3. **Scalability**: Parameterized for different environments\n4. **Integration**: Works with existing monitoring infrastructure\n5. **Documentation**: Clear decision criteria and actions\n\nThis procedure transforms ad-hoc log analysis into a systematic, repeatable process that can be applied consistently across different systems and scenarios.\n<<<END_SUMMARY_MD>>>\n\n<<<MANIFEST_CSV>>>\npath,type\n/tmp_workspace/results/result.json,json\n/tmp_workspace/results/summary.md,markdown\n/tmp_workspace/results/manifest.csv,csv\n<<<END_MANIFEST_CSV>>>","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.15.0","hostname":"unknown","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-04-19T03:56:00.049Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///opt/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-Cgmckbux.js:153:46","fileName":"subsystem-Cgmckbux.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-Cgmckbux.js:153","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"153","filePath":"/opt/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-Cgmckbux.js","filePathWithLine":"/opt/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-Cgmckbux.js:153","method":"console.log"}},"time":"2026-04-19T03:56:00.049+00:00"}
